.TH "bnx2x_func_reset_port" 9 "bnx2x_func_reset_port" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
bnx2x_func_reset_port \- reset HW at port stage
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" bnx2x_func_reset_port
.BI "(struct bnx2x *bp "  ","
.BI "const struct bnx2x_func_sp_drv_ops *drv "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "bp" 12
device handle
.IP "drv" 12
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Reset HW at FW_MSG_CODE_DRV_UNLOAD_PORT stage: reset
FUNCTION-only and PORT-only HW blocks.

!!!IMPORTANT!!!

It's important to call reset_port before \fBreset_func\fP as the last thing
reset_func does is \fBpf_disable\fP thus disabling PGLUE_B, which
makes impossible any DMAE transactions.
